{"articles_and_essays": null, "calendar_url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn95047334/?st=calendar", "cite_this": {"apa": "(1937, December 16)  <cite>Gadsden County times</cite>. Retrieved from the Library of Congress, https://www.loc.gov/item/sn95047334/1937-12-16/ed-1/.", "chicago": "<cite>Gadsden County times</cite>. (Quincy, FL), Dec. 16 1937. https://www.loc.gov/item/sn95047334/1937-12-16/ed-1/.", "mla": "<cite>Gadsden County times</cite>. (Quincy, FL) 16 Dec. 1937, p. 2. Retrieved from the Library of Congress, www.loc.gov/item/sn95047334/1937-12-16/ed-1/."}, "fulltext_service": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/fu/batch_fu_hastings_ver02/data/sn95047334/00529042401/1937121601/0852.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "item": {"_version_": 1855546322470305792, "access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/sn95047334/1937-12-16/ed-1/", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn95047334/1937-12-16/ed-1/"], "batch": ["fu_hastings_ver02"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/florida/", "2/united states/florida/gadsden/", "3/united states/florida/gadsden/quincy/"], "contributor_names": ["University of Florida"], "contributors": [{"university of florida": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=contributor:university+of+florida&fo=json"}], "created_published": ["Quincy, Fla., December 16, 1937"], "date": "1937-12-16", "date_issued": "1937-12-16", "dates": [{"1937-12-16": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?dates=1937-12-16/1937-12-16&fo=json"}], "dates_of_publication": "190?-current", "description": ["Quincy, Fla."], "digital_id": ["http://ufdc.ufl.edu/UF00028297"], "digitized": true, "digitized_label": "Present", "display_offsite": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-01-27T17:02:10.527Z", "extract_urls": ["file:/service/ndnp//fu/batch_fu_hastings_ver02/data/sn95047334/00529042401/1937121601/1937121601_1.xml#ndnp/fu"], "format": [{"newspaper": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=original_format:newspaper&fo=json"}], "genre": ["Newspapers"], "group": ["ndnp/fu", "university-of-florida-awardee"], "hassegments": true, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn95047334/1937-12-16/ed-1/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:fu:batch_fu_hastings_ver02:data:sn95047334:00529042401:1937121601:0851/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=471&w=327", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:fu:batch_fu_hastings_ver02:data:sn95047334:00529042401:1937121601:0851/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=942&w=655"], "index": 2, "item": {"batch": ["fu_hastings_ver02"], "contributor_names": ["University of Florida"], "created_published": ["Quincy, Fla., December 16, 1937"], "date": "190u", "date_issued": "1937-12-16", "dates": ["1937-12-16"], "digital_id": ["http://ufdc.ufl.edu/UF00028297"], "digitized_label": "Present", "format": ["newspaper"], "genre": ["Newspapers"], "language": ["eng"], "library_of_congress_control_number": "sn95047334", "location": ["Quincy (Fla.)", "Gadsden County (Fla.)", "Florida--Gadsden County", "Florida--Quincy"], "medium": "16 pages", "newspaper_title": ["Gadsden County times"], "notes": ["Weekly", "\"Consolidated with the Quincy moon\" <1909>.", "Publishers: R.E.L. McFarlin, <1913-1917>; R.L. Swerger, <1918-1926>.", "Also issued on microfilm from the University of Florida.", "Description based on: Vol. 6, no. 10 (Mar. 8, 1907).", "Latest issue consulted: Vol. 95, no. 47 (Nov. 30, 1995)."], "other_formats": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp//fu/batch_fu_hastings_ver02/data/sn95047334/00529042401/1937121601/1937121601_1.xml", "http://lccn.loc.gov/sn95047334/marcxml"], "place_of_publication": "Quincy, Fla.", "raw_lccn": "sn 95047334 ", "reel_numbers": ["00529042401"], "source_group": "ndnp/fu", "subjects": ["Quincy (Fla.)--Newspapers", "Gadsden County (Fla.)--Newspapers", "Florida--Gadsden County", "Florida--Quincy", "United States--Florida--Gadsden--Quincy"], "summary": ["The Gadsden County (FL) Times [LCCN: sn95047334] is published in Quincy (FL), the seat of Gadsden County (FL) government. The title dates from the early 1900s and continues publishing to this day (ca. 2008). The Gadsden County Times was preceded variously by the Quincy (FL) Herald [LCCN: sn95047329], the Quincy Florida Herald [LCCN: sn95047330], and the Gadsden County (FL) Herald [LCCN: sn95047333]. Gadsden County was created in 1823 as Florida's fifth county, once known as Middle Florida. When established, the County ran from Georgia to the Gulf of Mexico. Today (ca. 2008), it runs half that length. Quincy was incorporated as the County seat in 1828. Both the Quincy area and Gadsden County continue to be primarily agricultural (ca. 2008), as they were when established. The newspaper continues to report heavily on agricultural and local issues. Their early economies were dominated by cotton and tobacco crops. By the turn of the 20th century and the newspaper's founding, the area was linked into a broader southern U.S. economy by the Georgia, Florida, and Alabama Railway. And, the Railway's old Seaboard Air line connected Quincy directly to Florida's capital city, Tallahassee. Gadsden County is and has been unique in both northern Florida and Florida in general. In the northern counties of Florida's panhandle, it has continuously voted overwhelming from the Democrat Party. In the whole of Florida, it is and has been unique in that it is majority African American. The same is true of Quincy. The County was named for James Gadsden, Army engineer and later diplomat. James Gadsden is best known for the Gadsden Purchase from Mexico of an area in present day southern Arizona and New Mexico. Gadsden was also instrumental in negotiations with the Seminole Indians for relinquishment of their lands in exchange for land west of the Mississippi River. This effort resulted in the 1832 Treaty of Payne's Landing repudiated by most Seminoles.--E. Kesse, University of Florida Digital Library Center."], "title": "Gadsden County times (Quincy, Fla.), December 16, 1937"}, "language": ["english"], "languages": [{"english": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=language:english&fo=json"}], "library_of_congress_control_number": "sn95047334", "location": ["gadsden county", "united states", "gadsden", "florida", "quincy"], "location_city": ["quincy"], "location_country": ["united states"], "location_county": ["gadsden"], "location_state": ["florida"], "locations": [{"florida": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=location:florida&fo=json"}, {"gadsden": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=location:gadsden&fo=json"}, {"gadsden county": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=location:gadsden+county&fo=json"}, {"quincy": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=location:quincy&fo=json"}, {"united states": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=location:united+states&fo=json"}], "locations_city": [{"quincy": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=location_city:quincy&fo=json"}], "locations_country": [{"united states": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=location_country:united+states&fo=json"}], "locations_county": [{"gadsden": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=location_county:gadsden&fo=json"}], "locations_state": [{"florida": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=location_state:florida&fo=json"}], "medium": "16 pages", "method": "mets_filesec", "mime_type": ["image/jp2", "application/pdf", "text/xml", "image/jpeg"], "newspaper_title": ["Gadsden County times"], "notes": ["Weekly", "\"Consolidated with the Quincy moon\" <1909>.", "Publishers: R.E.L. McFarlin, <1913-1917>; R.L. Swerger, <1918-1926>.", "Also issued on microfilm from the University of Florida.", "Description based on: Vol. 6, no. 10 (Mar. 8, 1907).", "Latest issue consulted: Vol. 95, no. 47 (Nov. 30, 1995)."], "number": ["sn95047334", "00529042401", "1"], "number_edition": ["1"], "number_lccn": ["sn95047334"], "number_reel": ["00529042401"], "numeric_shelf_id": 193712161, "online_format": ["image", "pdf", "online text"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_formats": [{"label": "MODSXML Record", "link": "//tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp//fu/batch_fu_hastings_ver02/data/sn95047334/00529042401/1937121601/1937121601_1.xml"}, {"label": "MARCXML Record", "link": "//lccn.loc.gov/sn95047334/marcxml"}], "partof": [{"count": 1866, "title": "gadsden county times (quincy, fla.) 190?-current", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=partof:gadsden+county+times+%28quincy,+fla.%29+190%3F-current&fo=json"}, {"count": 3203926, "title": "chronicling america", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/collections/chronicling-america/?fo=json"}, {"count": 3225157, "title": "serial and government publications division", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=partof:serial+and+government+publications+division&fo=json"}], "partof_collection": ["chronicling america"], "partof_division": ["serial and government publications division"], "partof_title": ["gadsden county times (quincy, fla.) 190?-current"], "place_of_publication": "Quincy, Fla.", "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "raw_lccn": "sn 95047334 ", "reel_numbers": ["00529042401"], "resources": [{"files": 16, "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:fu:batch_fu_hastings_ver02:data:sn95047334:00529042401:1937121601:0851/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn95047334/1937-12-16/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}], "rights": ["<p>The Library of Congress believes that the newspapers in Chronicling America are in the public domain or have no known copyright restrictions.  Newspapers published in the United States more than 95 years ago are in the public domain in their entirety. Any newspapers in Chronicling America that were published less than 95 years ago are also believed to be in the public domain, but may contain some copyrighted third party materials. Researchers using newspapers published less than 95 years ago should be alert for modern content (for example, registered and renewed for copyright and published with notice) that may be copyrighted.  Responsibility for making an independent legal assessment of an item and securing any necessary permissions ultimately rests with persons desiring to use the item.</p>\n<p>The NEH awardee responsible for producing each digital object is presented in the Chronicling America page display, below the page image  \u2013 e.g. Image produced by the Library of Congress. For more information on current NDNP awardees, see <a href=\"https://www.loc.gov/ndnp/listawardees.html\">https://www.loc.gov/ndnp/listawardees.html</a>.</p>\n<p>For more information on Library of Congress policies and disclaimers regarding rights and reproductions, see <a href=\"https://www.loc.gov/homepage/legal.html\">https://www.loc.gov/homepage/legal.html</a></p>"], "score": 14.45633, "shard": "04", "shelf_id": "sn95047334, 1937-12-16, Edition 1", "site": ["chroniclingamerica"], "source_group": "ndnp/fu", "source_modified": "2000-01-01T12:00:00Z", "subject": ["gadsden county", "united states", "gadsden", "gadsden county (fla.)", "florida", "newspapers", "quincy (fla.)", "quincy"], "subject_headings": ["Quincy (Fla.)--Newspapers", "Gadsden County (Fla.)--Newspapers", "Florida--Gadsden County", "Florida--Quincy", "United States--Florida--Gadsden--Quincy"], "subjects": [{"florida": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:florida&fo=json"}, {"gadsden": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:gadsden&fo=json"}, {"gadsden county": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:gadsden+county&fo=json"}, {"gadsden county (fla.)": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:gadsden+county+%28fla.%29&fo=json"}, {"newspapers": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:newspapers&fo=json"}, {"quincy": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:quincy&fo=json"}, {"quincy (fla.)": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:quincy+%28fla.%29&fo=json"}, {"united states": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:united+states&fo=json"}], "summary": ["The Gadsden County (FL) Times [LCCN: sn95047334] is published in Quincy (FL), the seat of Gadsden County (FL) government. The title dates from the early 1900s and continues publishing to this day (ca. 2008). The Gadsden County Times was preceded variously by the Quincy (FL) Herald [LCCN: sn95047329], the Quincy Florida Herald [LCCN: sn95047330], and the Gadsden County (FL) Herald [LCCN: sn95047333]. Gadsden County was created in 1823 as Florida's fifth county, once known as Middle Florida. When established, the County ran from Georgia to the Gulf of Mexico. Today (ca. 2008), it runs half that length. Quincy was incorporated as the County seat in 1828. Both the Quincy area and Gadsden County continue to be primarily agricultural (ca. 2008), as they were when established. The newspaper continues to report heavily on agricultural and local issues. Their early economies were dominated by cotton and tobacco crops. By the turn of the 20th century and the newspaper's founding, the area was linked into a broader southern U.S. economy by the Georgia, Florida, and Alabama Railway. And, the Railway's old Seaboard Air line connected Quincy directly to Florida's capital city, Tallahassee. Gadsden County is and has been unique in both northern Florida and Florida in general. In the northern counties of Florida's panhandle, it has continuously voted overwhelming from the Democrat Party. In the whole of Florida, it is and has been unique in that it is majority African American. The same is true of Quincy. The County was named for James Gadsden, Army engineer and later diplomat. James Gadsden is best known for the Gadsden Purchase from Mexico of an area in present day southern Arizona and New Mexico. Gadsden was also instrumental in negotiations with the Seminole Indians for relinquishment of their lands in exchange for land west of the Mississippi River. This effort resulted in the 1832 Treaty of Payne's Landing repudiated by most Seminoles.--E. Kesse, University of Florida Digital Library Center."], "timestamp": "2026-01-28T07:54:27.093Z", "title": "Gadsden County times (Quincy, Fla.), December 16, 1937", "type": ["issue"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn95047334/1937-12-16/ed-1/"}, "locations": null, "method": "mets_filesec", "more_like_this": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/sn95047334/"], "batch": ["fu_hastings_ver02"], "campaigns": [], "date": "190?", "description": ["The Gadsden County (FL) Times [LCCN: sn95047334] is published in Quincy (FL), the seat of Gadsden County (FL) government. The title dates from the early 1900s and continues publishing to this day (ca. 2008). The Gadsden County Times was preceded variously by the Quincy (FL) Herald [LCCN: sn95047329], the Quincy Florida Herald [LCCN: sn95047330], and the Gadsden County (FL) Herald [LCCN: sn95047333]. Gadsden County was created in 1823 as Florida's fifth county, once known as Middle Florida. When established, the County ran from Georgia to the Gulf of Mexico. Today (ca. 2008), it runs half that length. Quincy was incorporated as the County seat in 1828. Both the Quincy area and Gadsden County continue to be primarily agricultural (ca. 2008), as they were when established. The newspaper continues to report heavily on agricultural and local issues. Their early economies were dominated by cotton and tobacco crops. By the turn of the 20th century and the newspaper's founding, the area was linked into a broader southern U.S. economy by the Georgia, Florida, and Alabama Railway. And, the Railway's old Seaboard Air line connected Quincy directly to Florida's capital city, Tallahassee. Gadsden County is and has been unique in both northern Florida and Florida in general. In the northern counties of Florida's panhandle, it has continuously voted overwhelming from the Democrat Party. In the whole of Florida, it is and has been unique in that it is majority African American. The same is true of Quincy. The County was named for James Gadsden, Army engineer and later diplomat. James Gadsden is best known for the Gadsden Purchase from Mexico of an area in present day southern Arizona and New Mexico. Gadsden was also instrumental in negotiations with the Seminole Indians for relinquishment of their lands in exchange for land west of the Mississippi River. This effort resulted in the 1832 Treaty of Payne's Landing repudiated by most Seminoles.--E. Kesse, University of Florida Digital Library Center."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-06-05T18:25:17.596Z", "group": ["newspaper-titles", "ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn95047334/", "image_url": [], "index": 2, "language": ["english"], "latlong": [30.588163, -84.581462], "location": ["gadsden county", "united states", "gadsden", "florida", "quincy"], "location_str": "", "lonlat": [-84.581462, 30.588163], "number": ["1865", "sn95047333", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn95047334/1963-12-26/ed-1/", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn95047334/1907-03-08/ed-1/", "1", "1445941", "2025-05-23t21:30:26", "online resource", "sn95047334"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["chronicling america", "serial and government publications division", "gadsden county times (quincy, fla.) 190?-current", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 83.90408, "shelf_id": "http://lccn.loc.gov/sn95047334", "site": ["chroniclingamerica", "usnd"], "subject": ["gadsden county", "united states", "gadsden", "gadsden county (fla.)", "florida", "newspapers", "quincy (fla.)", "quincy"], "timestamp": "2026-07-18T09:36:43.276Z", "title": "Gadsden County times", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn95047334/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/sn95047329/"], "batch": ["fu_freeport_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1877", "description": ["Weekly Began Jan. 1, 1877. Description based on: Vol. 9, no. 13 (Mar. 25, 1885). Latest issue consulted: Vo